---
description: Generic Rules
alwaysApply: true
---

- Don't be sycophantic
- Always be clear and precise
- Don't use filler words and sentences
- Always say the truth
- Always be fact oriented and data driven
- Avoid `else` when possible: prefer guard clauses and early returns; for two-way setup, use mutually exclusive `if` blocks or extract a small method. See **Control flow: avoid `else` when possible** in [clean-code.mdc](clean-code.mdc).

## Running Tool Commands

The repo is set up for Docker Compose: the **host** service runs the ASP.NET Core app; the **csharp** service is the .NET SDK dev image (same as `Dockerfile.dev` / `make build-dev-image`) and stays idle so you can exec into it.

- Always run build, test, and format commands **in the `csharp` container** (working directory `/src`).
- To start the stack run `make up` (starts **host** and **csharp**). For a long-lived SDK shell use `make shell` instead (standalone `docker run`, not Compose).
- To run a one-off command: `docker compose exec -T csharp <command>` (e.g. `docker compose exec -T csharp dotnet --version`).
- To run tests: `docker compose exec -T csharp dotnet test CSharpModulith.sln -c Release`
- For merged Cobertura + HTML coverage (Coverlet + local ReportGenerator tool): `make test-coverage` → `coverage/coverage.cobertura.xml`, `coverage/html/index.html`, raw inputs under `coverage/raw/`
- To build the solution: `docker compose exec -T csharp dotnet build CSharpModulith.sln -c Release`
- To apply formatting (whitespace / style where configured): `docker compose exec -T csharp dotnet format`
- If bind-mount file ownership errors appear when building the **csharp** image, set `DEV_UID` / `DEV_GID` to your user before `docker compose build csharp`, e.g. `DEV_UID=$(id -u) DEV_GID=$(id -g) docker compose build csharp`.

## After Making changes

- Before finishing a task you SHOULD run `dotnet format` (in the **csharp** container) so style stays consistent
- Before finishing a task you MUST run `dotnet build` on the solution; fix any build or analyzer errors
- Before finishing a task you MUST run `dotnet test` on the solution; fix failing tests
